reks.com/images/page-hero-kilimanjaro.jpg","totalTime":"PT2H","estimatedCost":{"@type":"MonetaryAmount","currency":"USD","value":"150"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Nelson Mushi","url":"https://gokilimanjarotreks.com/about.html"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://gokilimanjarotreks.com/#organization"},"dateModified":"2026-06-14","step":[{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Required Documents","text":"Passport valid 6+ months past entry with 2 blank pages, printed Tanzania e-Visa confirmation, vaccination records, mandatory travel insurance covering trekking to 6,000 m including helicopter evacuation, printed flight itinerary."},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Clothing: Layered System","text":"Merino or synthetic base layers (top and bottom, no cotton), heavy fleece mid-layer, heavy down or synthetic puffy jacket rated to -15 C, waterproof and windproof hardshell jacket and pants. Layers go on and off through five climate zones."},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Extremities","text":"Hands: liner gloves plus heavy insulated outer gloves rated to -20 C. Head: wool beanie plus balaclava or buff covering the face. Feet: insulated waterproof hiking boots already broken in, 4-5 pairs heavy wool hiking socks, sock liners."},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Sleeping System","text":"Sleeping bag rated to -10 C minimum (rentable in Moshi for the climb), inflatable sleeping pad, silk or synthetic liner adds warmth and keeps the bag clean."},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Daypack Contents (30-40 L)","text":"Three-litre hydration capacity using Nalgene wide-mouth bottles plus a bladder, camera, snacks, headlamp with spare batteries, sunglasses category 4 UV, mineral SPF50 sunscreen, lip balm SPF30, personal first aid kit including blister care, hand warmers for summit night."},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Renting Gear in Moshi","text":"Full kit rental (sleeping bag, hardshell pants, down puffy, gloves, trekking poles, gaiters) is typically USD 100-150 for the climb. Discuss at the pre-trek briefing 